events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored 10 of his 32 points in overtime and the Detroit Pistons beat the San Antonio Spurs 138-131 in double overtime on Friday in a matchup of two of the NBA's worst teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bogandovic's 32 lead Pistons to double OT win over Spurs

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton had 22 points and 11 rebounds, Devin Booker scored 21 points and Chris Paul chipped in 19 as the Phoenix Suns cruised past the Indiana Pacers 117-104 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayton, Booker lead Suns past Pacers a day after Durant trade

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey provided a huge boost off the bench, scoring 27 points to help the Philadelphia 76ers rally from a 13-point deficit for a 119-108 win over the New York Knicks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey gives 76ers spark in 119-108 win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 41 points and Derrick White set new career highs with 33 points and eight 3-pointers to help the Boston Celtics hold off the Charlotte Hornets 127-116 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 41, White 33 as Celtics beat Hornets 127-116

headlines.description: - Lauri Markkanen and Walker Kessler each scored 23 points, Collin Sexton had 22 and the Utah Jazz overcame a 12-point deficit in the final five minutes to beat the Toronto Raptors 122-116 on Friday night and snap a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz rally to beat Raptors 122-116, snap 3-game skid

headlines.description: — The play was drawn up by assistant coach Chris Quinn during a Miami Heat scrimmage at the NBA restart bubble in 2020. A lob to the rim off an inbounds pass, and the result was a Jimmy Butler dunk.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler's dunk at end gives Heat 97-95 win over Rockets

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 32 points, nine rebounds and nine assists, Desmond Bane added 20 points and the Memphis Grizzlies built a big lead through the fourth quarter and coasted to a 128-107 win over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant has near triple-double as Grizzlies top Timberwolves

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell and the surging Cavaliers arrived in a city where they hadn't won in a decade and demonstrated why Cleveland was among just three teams that held off on making any deals at this week's NBA trade deadline.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 30, Cavs top Pelicans to win 5th straight

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander matched his career high with 44 points to lead the Oklahoma City Thunder to a 138-129 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander has 44, Thunder top Trail Blazers 138-129

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving had 25 points and 10 assists as the Dallas Mavericks beat the Sacramento Kings 122-114 on Friday night for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving's 25 points, 10 assists lead Mavericks over Kings

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 35 points and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Los Angeles Clippers 119-106...
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat Clippers 119-106 for 10th straight win
